{"title":"Choose your fighter: Ugly time-trial helmets official ranking","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/time-trial-helmets-ranking","date":1709648492000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/time-trial-helmets-ranking\">Choose your fighter: Ugly time-trial helmets official ranking</a></p>\n\n<p>Time-trials are not always the most exciting of stages at WorldTour races, but thanks to a plethora of increasingly bizarre ultra-aero helmets, we found ourselves transfixed by yesterdayâ€™s opening stage of Tirreno-Adriatico.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, we canâ€™t claim to know which helmet offers the greatest aerodynamic advantage, but we can adopt the mantle of <em>The Devil Wears Prada</em>â€™s Miranda Priestly and judge them on their aesthetics alone â€“ which is arguably the most important thing.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here, from the bad to the best, is the official ranking of the current crop of time-trial helmetsâ€¦</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/strade-bianche-gallery-2024\">Strade Bianche gallery: Pain faces of a dusty spring classic</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/2024-pro-cycling-kit\">All the 2024 WorldTour kits ranked from worst to first</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/best-bike-helmet\">Best bike helmet: Buyerâ€™s guide to road and gravel bike helmets from under Â£100</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/eurovision-performances-as-giro-ditalia-teams\">Eurovision performances as Giro dâ€™Italia teams</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<h2>#6: Visma-Lease a Bike, Giro â€“ The worst</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Visma-Lease-a-Bike-TT-helmets-Tirreno-970x647.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Visma-Lease-a-Bike-TT-helmets-Tirreno-970x646.jpeg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Visma-Lease-a-Bike-TT-helmets-Tirreno-300x200.jpeg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Visma-Lease-a-Bike-TT-helmets-Tirreno-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Visma-Lease-a-Bike-TT-helmets-Tirreno-1536x1024.jpeg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Visma-Lease-a-Bike-TT-helmets-Tirreno-2048x1365.jpeg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Visma-Lease-a-Bike-TT-helmets-Tirreno-750x500.jpeg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Visma-Lease-a-Bike-TT-helmets-Tirreno-1140x760.jpeg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Visma-Lease-a-Bike-TT-helmets-Tirreno-465x310.jpeg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Visma-Lease-a-Bike-TT-helmets-Tirreno-620x413.jpeg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Visma-Lease-a-Bike-TT-helmets-Tirreno-350x233.jpeg 350w\" /><figcaption>Bram Berkien</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The internet almost buckled under the weight of people hating on Visma-Lease a Bikeâ€™s new Giro TT helmet. It is simultaneously an aesthetic nightmare and a social media managerâ€™s engagement dream.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Visma-Lease-a-Bike-TT-Giro-helmets-970x647.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Visma-Lease-a-Bike-TT-Giro-helmets-970x646.jpeg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Visma-Lease-a-Bike-TT-Giro-helmets-300x200.jpeg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Visma-Lease-a-Bike-TT-Giro-helmets-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Visma-Lease-a-Bike-TT-Giro-helmets-1536x1025.jpeg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Visma-Lease-a-Bike-TT-Giro-helmets-750x500.jpeg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Visma-Lease-a-Bike-TT-Giro-helmets-1140x760.jpeg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Visma-Lease-a-Bike-TT-Giro-helmets-465x310.jpeg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Visma-Lease-a-Bike-TT-Giro-helmets-620x413.jpeg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Visma-Lease-a-Bike-TT-Giro-helmets-350x233.jpeg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Visma-Lease-a-Bike-TT-Giro-helmets.jpeg 2048w\" /><figcaption>Bram Berkien</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The team debuted their new helmet designs before the opening stage of Tirreno-Adriatico yesterday, a 10km individual time-trial ultimately won by Juan Ayuso of UAE Team Emirates. Visma-Lease a Bikeâ€™s highest-placed rider was Jonas Vingegaard in 9th.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The shape creates a bulbous â€˜helmetâ€™ stretching to the sky like a Borsoi dog looking up for treats. Even if it doesnâ€™t generate more speed, it has already paid its way in generating exposure. But is that worth the memes? </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>#5: Uno-X, Sweet Protection â€“ Thumbs down</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"546\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/2mGpbVwx4tUdCegDVYox3E-970-80.jpg.webp\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/2mGpbVwx4tUdCegDVYox3E-970-80.jpg.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/2mGpbVwx4tUdCegDVYox3E-970-80.jpg-300x169.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/2mGpbVwx4tUdCegDVYox3E-970-80.jpg-768x432.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/2mGpbVwx4tUdCegDVYox3E-970-80.jpg-750x422.webp 750w\" /><figcaption>Uno-X</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Before Visma-Lease a Bike came and stole the top spot at yesterdayâ€™s TT, the prize for worst helmet in the peloton was held by Uno-X. Debuting to much chatter at the Volta ao Algarve last year, the Sweet Protection â€˜Redeemer 2Viâ€™ lid features flared sides like a pair of â€™70s jeans.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"646\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Uno-X-helmet-970x646.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Uno-X-helmet-970x646.jpeg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Uno-X-helmet-300x200.jpeg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Uno-X-helmet-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Uno-X-helmet-1536x1023.jpeg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Uno-X-helmet-750x500.jpeg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Uno-X-helmet-1140x759.jpeg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Uno-X-helmet-465x310.jpeg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Uno-X-helmet-620x413.jpeg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Uno-X-helmet-350x233.jpeg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Uno-X-helmet.jpeg 2048w\" /><figcaption>Uno-X</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The effect is Star Wars stormtrooper meets bullfrog, but at least it matches the teamâ€™s socks, so thatâ€™s at least two fashion points gained back.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>#4: Bahrain-Victorious, Rudy Project â€“ Still not a fan</h2>\n\n\n\n<div><blockquote><p>The new Bahrain Victorious time trial helmets have gone under the radar <img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/14.0.0/72x72/1f440.png\" alt=\"ðŸ‘€\" /><a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/TirrenoAdriatico?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\" target=\"_blank\">#TirrenoAdriatico</a> | Watch on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/discoveryplusUK?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\" target=\"_blank\">@discoveryplusUK</a> and Eurosport <a href=\"https://t.co/VbtR1PPev5\" target=\"_blank\">pic.twitter.com/VbtR1PPev5</a></p>â€” Eurosport (@eurosport) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/eurosport/status/1764679541534969856?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\" target=\"_blank\">March 4, 2024</a></blockquote> </div>\n\n\n\n<p>With so much attention directed at Visma-Lease a Bikeâ€™s abomination, Bahrain-Victoriousâ€™s new helmet that also debuted during Stage 1 of Tirreno-Adriatico passed with barely a mention.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>But it didnâ€™t escape <em>our</em> attention. Itâ€™s essentially a bowling ball glued onto a plastic light shade, creating an aesthetic so ugly that they felt the need to give it a grey camouflage design in the hope that no one would notice it.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>#3: Soudal-QuickStep, Specialized â€“ Getting warmer</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"602\" height=\"338\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/florian-senechal-2022-tour-de-frane-gcn.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/florian-senechal-2022-tour-de-frane-gcn.jpeg 602w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/florian-senechal-2022-tour-de-frane-gcn-300x168.jpeg 300w\" /><figcaption>GCN+/Eurosport</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>A helmet and snood combination first seen at the 2022 <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/tour-de-france\" target=\"_blank\">Tour de France</a>. We quite like this one. <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/soudal-quickstep\" target=\"_blank\">Soudal-QuickStepâ€™s</a> Specialized TT helmet is bulbous but quite pleasantly shaped in a way that makes it look functional in a fashionable way.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Then you see the balaclava. Specialized says it is â€˜designed to smooth airflow around and through the brandâ€™s helmetsâ€™ by flattening areas such as hair and ears. We say it looks like the teamâ€™s collective grandmothers have insisted they wear them to prevent them catching a chill. The snood steals the show, and this article is about helmets. Perhaps thatâ€™s even worse a crime than being a fashion disaster.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>#2: EF Education-Cannondale and EF Education-EasyPost, Poc â€“ Almost there (Hi Barbie!)</h2>\n\n\n\n<div><blockquote><div> <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/p/Cr3gg-FsII3/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;utm_campaign=loading\" target=\"_blank\"> <div> <div></div> <div> <div></div> <div></div></div></div><div></div> <div></div><div> <div>View this post on Instagram</div></div><div></div> <div><div> <div></div> <div></div> <div></div></div><div> <div></div> <div></div></div><div> <div></div> <div></div> <div></div></div></div> <div> <div></div> <div></div></div></a><p><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/p/Cr3gg-FsII3/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;utm_campaign=loading\" target=\"_blank\">A post shared by Team TTT (@team_ts_ttt)</a></p></div></blockquote> </div>\n\n\n\n<p>The now-discontinued EF Education Tibco-SVB team used to wear a beautiful Procen TT helmet from Poc, the menâ€™s <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/ef-education-easypost\" target=\"_blank\">EF Education-EasyPost</a> team also wearing it at the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/giro-ditalia\" target=\"_blank\">Giro dâ€™Italia</a> in 2023. Anything Barbie pink gets a thumbs-up. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Poc has caused more of a stir with a TT-inspired <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/pro-cycling-tech-leaks\" target=\"_blank\">unreleased aero road helmet</a> that covers the top of the ridersâ€™ ears and has been worn by both EF Education-EasyPost and the EF Education-Cannondale squad, which is similar to the Procen. I prefer the older design, but donâ€™t tell them that. They probably wonâ€™t hear anyway, their ears being covered and all.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>#1: Ineos Grenadiers, Kask â€“ The best</h2>\n\n\n\n<div><blockquote><p><a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/UCIHourRecord?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\" target=\"_blank\">#UCIHourRecord</a> Helmet <img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/14.0.0/72x72/2705.png\" alt=\"âœ…\" /><br /><br />The <a href=\"https://twitter.com/Kask_cycling?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\" target=\"_blank\">@Kask_cycling</a> Bambino Pro Evo, combined with the latest Aero Pro Visor, is a thing of beauty <img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/14.0.0/72x72/1f60d.png\" alt=\"ðŸ˜\" /><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/14.0.0/72x72/1f1ee-1f1f9.png\" alt=\"ðŸ‡®ðŸ‡¹\" /><br /><br />R&amp;D <img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/14.0.0/72x72/1f91d.png\" alt=\"ðŸ¤\" /> Performance <img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/14.0.0/72x72/1f91d.png\" alt=\"ðŸ¤\" /> Speed. It's all yours, <a href=\"https://twitter.com/GannaFilippo?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\" target=\"_blank\">@GannaFilippo</a>! <a href=\"https://t.co/GBStc0P0Pb\" target=\"_blank\">pic.twitter.com/GBStc0P0Pb</a></p>â€” INEOS Grenadiers (@INEOSGrenadiers) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/INEOSGrenadiers/status/1577948512574136321?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\" target=\"_blank\">October 6, 2022</a></blockquote> </div>\n\n\n\n<p>Kask showed how time-trial helmets should be done with this special edition of the Kask Bambino Pro Evo worn by Filippo Ganna during his successful UCI Hour Record attempt. Admittedly, the Italian could wear a bucket on his head and still look sleek, but the Bambino Pro Evo is on the right side of Darth Vader-esque.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Kask-Bambino-Pro-Evo-aerodynamic-TT-custom-helmet-with-new-Aero-Pro-Visor-jpg-970x647.webp\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Kask-Bambino-Pro-Evo-aerodynamic-TT-custom-helmet-with-new-Aero-Pro-Visor-jpg-970x646.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Kask-Bambino-Pro-Evo-aerodynamic-TT-custom-helmet-with-new-Aero-Pro-Visor-jpg-300x200.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Kask-Bambino-Pro-Evo-aerodynamic-TT-custom-helmet-with-new-Aero-Pro-Visor-jpg-768x512.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Kask-Bambino-Pro-Evo-aerodynamic-TT-custom-helmet-with-new-Aero-Pro-Visor-jpg-1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Kask-Bambino-Pro-Evo-aerodynamic-TT-custom-helmet-with-new-Aero-Pro-Visor-jpg-750x500.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Kask-Bambino-Pro-Evo-aerodynamic-TT-custom-helmet-with-new-Aero-Pro-Visor-jpg-1140x760.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Kask-Bambino-Pro-Evo-aerodynamic-TT-custom-helmet-with-new-Aero-Pro-Visor-jpg-465x310.webp 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Kask-Bambino-Pro-Evo-aerodynamic-TT-custom-helmet-with-new-Aero-Pro-Visor-jpg-620x413.webp 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Kask-Bambino-Pro-Evo-aerodynamic-TT-custom-helmet-with-new-Aero-Pro-Visor-jpg-350x233.webp 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Kask-Bambino-Pro-Evo-aerodynamic-TT-custom-helmet-with-new-Aero-Pro-Visor-jpg.webp 1800w\" /><figcaption>Chris Auld, Ineos Grenadiers</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Our only gripe â€“ the clear visor. Weâ€™re not a fan of being able to see ridersâ€™ eyes during a time-trial effort. It feels too intimate, so please use a tinted visor in future. Although in Gannaâ€™s case, he was going so fast that we couldnâ€™t see them anyway.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/GH1XtBaXcAAoG5k-1-970x647.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/GH1XtBaXcAAoG5k-1-970x646.jpeg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/GH1XtBaXcAAoG5k-1-300x200.jpeg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/GH1XtBaXcAAoG5k-1-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/GH1XtBaXcAAoG5k-1-1536x1024.jpeg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/GH1XtBaXcAAoG5k-1-2048x1366.jpeg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/GH1XtBaXcAAoG5k-1-750x500.jpeg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/GH1XtBaXcAAoG5k-1-1140x760.jpeg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/GH1XtBaXcAAoG5k-1-465x310.jpeg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/GH1XtBaXcAAoG5k-1-620x413.jpeg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/GH1XtBaXcAAoG5k-1-350x233.jpeg 350w\" /><figcaption>Ineos Grenadiers</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Hour Record aside, the Ineos Grenadiers team use the Bambino Pro Evo helmet for their time-trialling on the road. Ganna has an advantage in this area, the Italian ITT Champion combining his tricolour kit with the same design on his helmet and finished second wearing it in the Tirreno-Adriatico ITT.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Cycling helmets have advanced over the years. Not only in terms of aerodynamic efficiency or offering a better protection, but thereâ€™s a shift towards space helmets that look much more suited to defending the galaxy than riding a bike during time-trials. Maybe theyâ€™re preparing for something we donâ€™t know. Either way, aesthetically pleasing most are not. Unless youâ€™re an Italian Champion. Then carry on.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/time-trial-helmets-ranking\">Choose your fighter: Ugly time-trial helmets official ranking</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a>.</p>","author":"Robyn Davidson &#124; Editorial Assistant","siteTitle":"Cyclist.co.uk","siteHash":"561486e7070fa5351de9318ad0fa26c2a39332acba5fc7c7d1694a01d53d431e","entryHash":"bd7d659d1361f5cff551f3d9c6f0cb4c53331dba813cecd4a59aa1fa69c3de93","category":"Cycling"}